---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import FormalBrief from '../components/LayoutPrimitives/FormalBrief.astro';
import ValidationTable from '../components/LayoutPrimitives/ValidationTable.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Investor Relations | Lupine">
  <FormalBrief 
    title="Institutional Validation Manuscript"
    subtitle="Empirical validation metrics establishing the Atlas Distill technological moat"
    sealText="CONFIDENTIAL // PERFORMANCE METRICS"
  >
    <Fragment slot="marginalia">
      <span class="citation-note"><strong>The Technological Moat:</strong> By automating the ingestion of NIST parameterizations, Lupine achieves a 10,000x acceleration in validation throughput compared to manual phenomenological fitting.</span>
      <span class="citation-note"><strong>Validation Protocol:</strong> All metrics shown are cross-validated using density functional theory (DFT) baseline references.</span>
    </Fragment>

    <h2>1. Atlas Engine Capabilities</h2>
    <p>The Atlas Distill engine represents a definitive leap in materials informatics. By converting the legacy empirical physics ecosystem into a unified, programmable data structure, we enable high-frequency algorithmic discovery of novel material properties.</p>
    
    <ValidationTable
      title="2. System Accuracy Benchmarks"
      summary="Crystalline Stability Metrics (NIST-884 Compliance). Utilizing Space Grotesk tabular figures for exact precision."
      headers={["PARAMETER (Silicon)", "DFT REFERENCE", "ATLAS OBSERVED", "DELTA (Δ)"]}
      rows={[
        { parameter: "Lattice Constant (a)", reference: "5.4309 Å", observed: "5.4312 Å", delta: "+0.0003", deltaState: "good" },
        { parameter: "Cohesive Energy", reference: "-4.63 eV/atom", observed: "-4.61 eV/atom", delta: "+0.02", deltaState: "warn" },
        { parameter: "Bulk Modulus (B)", reference: "97.6 GPa", observed: "97.8 GPa", delta: "+0.2", deltaState: "good" },
        { parameter: "C11 Elastic Constant", reference: "165.8 GPa", observed: "166.1 GPa", delta: "+0.3", deltaState: "warn" },
        { parameter: "Isotropic Strain Limit", reference: "0.0012", observed: "0.0014", delta: "+0.0002", deltaState: "warn" }
      ]}
    />

    <p style="margin-top: 2rem;">The table above demonstrates our ability to constrain predictions within extraordinarily tight tolerances. This level of empirical certainty is what defines our computational sovereignty strategy.</p>
  </FormalBrief>
</BaseLayout>
